Video from the BARPI

   Home

     * 28/11/2014
     * Non classé

   “Toxic alarm in the control room” presents an accident that occured in
   a French chemical plant in 2012, that led to the emission of a small
   amount of toxic gaz to the atmosphere. However, this accident could
   have had much more dramatic consequences. The mecanisms of this
   accident show that safety takes place in a technical but also a human
   context : the display of a false information parameter led the control
   room operators to a dangerous decision that worsened the accident and
   required the intervention of the last barriers of the “defense in
   depth” safety system.

